      • onInitializationStarted

        Called when initial static period starts so that base noise level starts being estimated.

      • onInitializationCompleted

        void onInitializationCompleted​(StaticIntervalDetector detected,
                               double baseNoiseLevel)
        Called when initial static period successfully completes and base noise level is estimated so that static and dynamic periods can be detected.
        Parameters:
        detected - detector that raised the event.
        baseNoiseLevel - base accelerometer noise level expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).

      • onError

        void onError​(StaticIntervalDetector detector,
             double accumulatedNoiseLevel,
             double instantaneousNoiseLevel,
             StaticIntervalDetector.ErrorReason reason)
        Called when an error is detected during initialization because there has been excessive movement forces.
        Parameters:
        detector - detector that raised the event.
        accumulatedNoiseLevel - accumulated noise level expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        instantaneousNoiseLevel - instantaneous noise level expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        reason - reason why error was detected.

      • onDynamicIntervalDetected

        void onDynamicIntervalDetected​(StaticIntervalDetector detector,
                               double avgSpecificForceX,
                               double avgSpecificForceY,
                               double avgSpecificForceZ)
        Called when a dynamic interval has been detected after initialization.
        Parameters:
        detector - detector that raised the event.
        avgSpecificForceX - average x-coordinate of specific force during last static period expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        avgSpecificForceY - average y-coordinate of specific force during last static period expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).
        avgSpecificForceZ - average z-coordinate of specific force during last static period expressed in meters per squared second (m/s^2).

        void onReset​(StaticIntervalDetector detector)
